 ## accESS mODIFIERS : 
  the special keywords we use with function , variables names, 
  1- Default : Default access modifiers are those which are only accessible within their class
  2- public : Can be accessible in its own file as well as in other files ( packages)
  3- protected : Can be accessible in its own file(packages) but in other files, only the subclasses can access.
  3- private : only accessible in its own class.constructor, and class method. can't accessible outside the class


  EnCAPSULATION: 
  EnCapSulation is the combining all of the data(propertes of our object in related class) and methods(functions we define within class), like properties and methods we have in our class. In simple words,
  creating classes and then creating objects through these classes is called Encapsulation.
  ## DATA HIDING
  Through Encapsulation, the concept of data hiding became possible, now how we hide data through encapsulation,
  let say I don't want to show some data of user outside the class, there I will use the protected /public/private depending upon the need. 
  we hide data using access modifiers.

  ## ABSTRACTION : 
  Abstraction is the proccess of only showing the important data to user  and keep hiding the non important data.
  Wherease Data hiding is the process of protecting data from untended changes from user. 


































  